Case Study

Today were studying a case.

Get Data

library(p8105.datasets)

data(nyc_airbnb)

nyc_airbnb =
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  rename(borough = neighbourhood_group) %>% 
  mutate(stars = review_scores_location / 2)

Brainstorm questions

  • what variables are relevant to higher review / scores?

  • what are the popular places to rent an Airbnb?

nyc_airbnb %>%
  group_by(neighbourhood, borough) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  summarize(n_obs = n()) %>%
  ungroup() %>% 
  group_by(borough) %>% 
  mutate(rank = min_rank(desc(n_obs))) %>% 
  filter(rank < 5) %>% 
  arrange(borough, desc(n_obs))

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = borough, fill = borough)) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(
    x = "Neighbourhood Group",
    y = "Number of Airbnbs",
    title = "Distribution of Airbnbs in New York City by Borough",
    ) +
  theme(
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    legend.title = element_blank()
    )

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Manhattan") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = neighbourhood)) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(
    x = "Neighbourhood",
    y = "Number of Airbnbs",
    title = "Distribution of Airbnbs in Manhattan, New York City",
    ) +
  theme(
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90),
    legend.title = element_blank()
    )

  • what proportion of hosts / locations are private rooms vs entire apartments?

  • what makes an airbnb more expensive?

Lets look at the price ..

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  group_by(borough, room_type) %>% 
  summarise(
    mean_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>% 
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = room_type,
    values_from = mean_price
  )
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'borough'. You can override using the

Look at price distributions

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Manhattan",
         price < 1000) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = price)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_grid(. ~ room_type)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

Price vs rating ?

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Manhattan") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = stars, y = price)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(. ~ room_type)

Somewhat fancy boxplot!

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Manhattan") %>% 
  group_by(neighbourhood) %>% 
  summarise(
    mean_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>% 
  arrange(desc(mean_price))
## # A tibble: 32  2

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Manhattan",
         room_type == "Entire home/apt") %>% 
  filter(price <= 1000) %>% 
  mutate(neighbourhood = fct_reorder(neighbourhood, price)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = neighbourhood, y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  coord_flip()

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Manhattan") %>% 
  filter(price <= 1000) %>% 
  mutate(neighbourhood = fct_reorder(neighbourhood, price)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = neighbourhood, y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  coord_flip() +
  facet_grid(. ~ room_type)

Price vs location

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Manhattan",
         room_type == "Entire home/apt") %>% 
  filter(price <= 1000) %>% 
  sample_n(1000) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = lat, y = long, color = price)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .5)

Lets make a map by leaflet

pal = colorNumeric("viridis", domain = c(0, 1000))

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Manhattan",
         room_type == "Entire home/apt") %>% 
  filter(price <= 1000) %>% 
  sample_n(1000) %>% 
  leaflet() %>% 
  addProviderTiles(providers$CartoDB.Positron) %>% 
  addCircleMarkers(~ lat, ~ long, radius = .5, color = ~ pal(price))
